The Chief Administrative Secretary in the Ministry of Education, Zakaria Kinuthia, revealed in a televised interview on December 14 that it will not be possible for students to observe social distancing when schools reopen in January.
He further clarified that if social distancing were to be observed fully as recommended by the Ministry of Health, the schools will only be able to accommodate one third of the total number of students.



