It is refreshing that a senior government official has for once come out candidly to make an admission that will go a long way to help all stakeholders make informed decisions on the way forward as January approaches instead of skirting around such an important issue.
In any case, even if the government were to provide resources for tripling infrastructure in all schools, we would lack the artisans to enable construction of these facilities at once and within time constraints.



