Before delving into the challenges that this decision will lead to in schools, I wish to raise two pertinent issues that are likely to arise from it. First, would the Ministry of Health overlook the requirement of social distancing for the sake of reopening, considering that schools have high population densities per square-kilometre, compared to other spaces in Kenya?
If not, which of the two positions will be adopted by the government? Secondly, international practice has indicated that when social distancing is ignored, Covid-19 infections go up.
Thanksgiving weekend
The infections in the US have increased tremendously to well over 200,000 per day just after the “thanksgiving” weekend when families are reported to have interacted closely. All countries in Europe, except Sweden and Finland, have instituted the most rigorous measures against social interaction in order to guard against a spike in infections over the Christmas and end-of-the-year festivities.



