That will be close to one third that would be ideal for social distancing. The remaining classes would then be recalled to schools by say, March, when vaccines will have been administered and normalcy attainable.
Internal measures
In the meantime, the boards of management of schools need to work on internal measures to control infections. They may need to dedicate several teachers to manage the Covid-19 protocols. This will include ensuring that a sufficient number of thermal guns are available and that all students are subjected to temperature checks every morning.
The same teachers would need to ensure that clean running water and soap as well as face masks are available at all times. The government on its part needs to ensure that capitation is released to schools on a timely basis to enable schools to buy whatever they must to combat the pandemic
The greatest challenge that should be a lesson to the country arising from this pandemic is lack of clean running water in schools. Conservative estimates are that up to 50 per cent of schools are water-deficient. The national and county governments need to synergise and prioritise provision of water henceforth. Meanwhile, 2021 will certainly be a difficult year for schools.



